snippet.title: It's 'right' for the government to 'park' the religious discrimination bill
snippet.description:
Political strategist Brigid Meney says she believes it's right for the government to "park" the religious discrimination bill while it sorts out its "problems". 

"I think the government has had to park this legislation because it's been pulled in a thousand different ways," Ms Meney told Sky News host Corey Bernardi. 

"And I think it's right to park it while they sort their own problems out with unity and the party room which seems to be quite an issue of late."

She said there has been a lot of concerns about the legislation from religious groups and communities including the Australian Christian Lobby. 

"But ultimately what I see half the problem is, is that religious communities, their values aren't represented within the parliamentarians ... and that's what needs to change."
